<font color="#FF0000">PEACE TAKES AN EFFORT</font><br>
<tt>Fri Nov 21 19:15:13 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Doc,<br><br>
I find pride in a lot of things in life.  I know from my experience when a bother is in pain and when he posts in certain ways as he struggles with his demons trying to survive.  You and I may not have this struggle to deal with, but others do.  It is at a time such as that when we must show our tolerance to get through the situation.  Tolerance is a huge effort here.  Emotions are strong and opinions often inflexible.<br><br>
I am very aware you did not request your own thread, but you could if you choose.  We move about this site making comment you and I and neither is always sure whose toes we are stepping on.  It takes a while to create a post and when turned loose it inserts itself into the middle of the scene.  We must learn to step around each other not bull headily crash through.  If you ignored us it would have no effect on the conversation.  As I have said it is a matter of choice we all make.  Choose wisely.<br><br>
Doc it is this depth and compassion that keeps me in step with my BOC.  Equally so when you post without malice I can have dialogue with you.  The struggle stems from the on again off again approach.<br><br>
I know what name-calling does.  Each of us has trigger words.  Draft Dodger is yours.  We know why ours hurt and you I assume are acutely aware why yours brings pain.  Let us say I understand very well.<br><br>
As for moving people's posts around, I would never make that choice.  The past has been filled with entire posts and excerpts being moved all over this site by both sides.  A method of expression that shouldn't be taken too seriously.  This site is for all to read.  Keeping things in perspective I assume.<br><br>
You asked could I be proud of the post directly above.  The answer is yes.  I know the man better than you do and I know why he posted it.  Brothers communicate in a manner that others cannot understand.  Let's just call it our language.<br><br>
I have always said respect is not something you may demand, but must be earned.<br><br>
Here is a quote I'll leave you with: Conscientious Objector<br><br>
And but for these vile guns,<br>
He would himself have been soldier.<br><br>
Shakespeare:  I King Henry IV, i, 3, 1597<br>

